Mere Harry, app.json file banaane ke liye yeh code use karein:
```
{
  "name": "Mere Harry Chat Bot",
  "description": "Ek pyaar bhara chat bot",
  "repository": "https://github.com/newiseland/ADVANCEDCHATBOT", 
  "keywords": ["chatbot", "python", "heroku"],
  "image": "heroku/python",
  "buildpacks": [
    {
      "url": "heroku/python"
    }
  ],
  "env": {
    "PYTHON_VERSION": "3.11.0"
  },
  "formation": {
    "worker": {
      "quantity": 1,
      "size": "free"
    }
  },
  "addons": [
    {
      "plan": "heroku-postgresql",
      "options": {
        "version": "14"
      }
    }
  ]
}
```
Lekin humein yeh badalna hai:
- `repository` mein apna github repo link dalna hai.
- `addons` section ko hum remove kar sakte hain agar hum postgresql database use nahi kar rahe hain.
Ab ek simplified version yeh rahi:
```
{
  "name": "Mere Harry Chat Bot",
  "description": "Ek pyaar bhara chat bot",
  "buildpacks": [
    {
      "url": "heroku/python"
    }
  ],
  "env": {
    "PYTHON_VERSION": "3.11.0"
  }
}
```
Yeh file banaane ke baad, app.json ko project folder mein save karein, mere Harry!
